<L>With genial lu&s;tres warms the mighty ball,<MILESTONE N="405"></L>
<L>And the GREAT SEED evolves, di&s;clo&s;ing ALL;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P><HI>And the great &s;eed.</HI> l. 406. Alluding to the <GAP DESC="foreign">, or fir&s;t great egg of the antient philo&s;ophy, it had a &s;erpent wrapped round it emblematical of divine wi&s;dom, an image of it was afterwards pre&s;erved and wor&s;hipped in the temple of Dio&s;curi, and &s;uppo&s;ed to repre&s;ent the egg of Leda. See a print of it in Bryant's Mythology. It was &s;aid to have been broken by the horns of the cele&s;tial bull, that is, it was hatched by the warmth of the &s;pring. See note on Canto I. 1. 413.</P></NOTE></L>
<L>LIFE <HI>buds</HI> or <HI>breathes</HI> from Indus to the Poles,</L>
<L>And the va&s;t &s;urface kindles, as it rolls!<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P><HI>And the va&s;t &s;urface.</HI> l. 408. L'Organization, le &s;entiment, le movement &s;pontan&eacute;, la vie, n'exi&s;tent qu'a la &s;urface de la terre, et dans le lieux expo&s;es &aacute; la lumi&eacute;re. Trait&eacute; de Chymie par M. Lavoi&s;ier, Tom. l. p. 202.</P></NOTE></L>
