<L>2. "Where cruder juices &s;well the leafy vein,</L>
<L>Stint the young germ, the tender blo&s;&s;om &s;tain;</L>
<L>On each lop'd &s;hoot a fo&s;ter &s;cion bind,</L>
<L>Pith pre&s;s'd to pith, and rind applied to rind,<MILESTONE N="480"></L>
<L>So &s;hall the trunk with loftier cre&s;t a&s;cend,</L>
