<L>Delighted BELLIS calls her infant throng.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P><HI>Bellis prolifera</HI> l. 144. Hen and chicken Dai&s;y; in this beautiful mon&s;ter not only the impletion or doubling of the petals takes place, as de&s;cribed in the note on Alcea; but a numerous circlet of le&s;s flowers on peduncles, or foot&s;talks, ri&s;e from the &s;ides of the calyx, and &s;urround the proliferous parent. The &s;ame occurs in Calendula, mari|gold; in Heracium, hawk-weed; and in Scabio&s;a, Scabious. Phil. Botan. p. 82.</P></NOTE></L>
