<L><PB N="157" REF="538">Or twine green oziers with the fragrant gale,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P><HI>The fragrant Gale.</HI> l. 151. The buds of the Myrica Gale po&s;&s;e&s;s an agreeable aromatic fragrance, and might be worth attending to as an article of the Materia Medica. Mr. Sparman &s;u&s;pects, that the green wax-like &s;ub&s;tance, with which at certain times of the year the berries of the Myrica cerifera, or candle-berry Myrtle, are covered, are depo|sited there by in&s;ects. It is u&s;ed by the inhabitants for making candles, which he &s;ays burn rather better than tho&s;e made of tallow. <HI>Voyage to the Cape,</HI> V. I. 345.</P></NOTE></L>
