<L>Daughter of Earth, the cha&s;te TRUFFELIA &s;miles;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P><HI>Truffelia.</HI> l. 392. (Lycoperdon Tuber) Truffle. Clande&s;tine marriage. This fungus never appears above ground, requiring little air, and perhaps no light. It is found by dogs or &s;wine, who hunt it by the &s;mell. Other plants, which have no buds or branches on their &s;tems, as the gra&s;&s;es, &s;hoot out numerous &s;toles or &s;cions underground; and this the more, as their tops or herbs are eaten by cattle, and thus pre&s;erve them&s;elves.</P></NOTE></L>
